obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8625)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8625&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Real Estate (Regulation`
  line `and Development) Act, 2016.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir^*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st May, 2016, vide notification No. S.O. 1544(E), Section 2, Sections 20 to 39, Sections 41 to 58, Sections 71 to 78, Sections`
  line `81 to 92 dated 26th April, 2016, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `1st May 2017, vide notification No. S.O. 1216(E), Section 3 to 19, Sections 40, Sections 59 to 71, Sections 79 to 80, dated 19th`
  line `April, 2016, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8626)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8626&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "adjudicating officer" means the adjudicating officer appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 71;`
  line
  line `(b) "advertisement" means any document described or issued as advertisement through any`
  line `medium and includes any notice, circular or other documents or publicity in any form, informing`
  line `persons about a real estate project, or offering for sale of a plot, building or apartment or inviting`
  line `persons to purchase in any manner such plot, building or apartment or to make advances or deposits`
  line `for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) "agreement for sale" means an agreement entered into between the promoter and the allottee;`
  line
  line `(d) "allottee" in relation to a real estate project, means the person to whom a plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, has been allotted, sold (whether as freehold or leasehold) or otherwise transferred by the promoter, and includes the person who subsequently acquires the said allotment through sale, transfer or otherwise but does not include a person to whom such plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, is given on rent;`
  line
  line `(e) "apartment" whether called block, chamber, dwelling unit, flat, office, showroom, shop, godown, premises, suit, tenement, unit or by any other name, means a separate and self-contained part of any immovable property, including one or more rooms or enclosed spaces, located on one or more floors or any part thereof, in a building or on a plot of land, used or intended to be used for any residential or commercial use such as residence, office, shop, showroom or godown or for carrying on any business, occupation, profession or trade, or for any other type of use ancillary to the purpose specified;`
  line
  line `(f)"Appellate Tribunal" means the Real Estate Appellate Tribunal established under section 43;`
  line
  line `(g) "appropriate Government" means in respect of matters relating to,---`
  line
  line `(i) the Union territory without Legislature, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Union territory of ^1[Puducherry and Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir], the`
  line `Union territory Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Union territory of Delhi, the Central Ministry of Urban Development;`
  line
  line `(iv) the State, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(h) "architect" means a person registered as an architect under the provisions of the Architects Act, 1972 (20 of 1972);`
  line
  line `(i) "Authority" means the Real Estate Regulatory Authority established under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(j) "building" includes any structure or erection or part of a structure or erection which is intended to be used for residential, commercial or for the purpose of any business, occupation, profession or trade, or for any other related purposes;`
  line
  line `(k) "carpet area" means the net usable floor area of an apartment, excluding the area covered by the external walls, areas under services shafts, exclusive balcony or verandah area and exclusive open terrace area, but includes the area covered by the internal partition walls of the apartment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this clause, the expression "exclusive balcony or verandah area" means the area of the balcony or verandah, as the case may be, which is appurtenant to the net usable floor area of an apartment, meant for the exclusive use of the allottee; and "exclusive open terrace area" means the area of open terrace which is appurtenant to the net usable floor area of an apartment, meant for the exclusive use of the allottee;`
  line
  line `(l) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Real Estate Regulatory Authority appointed under section 21;`
  line
  line `(m) "commencement certificate" means the commencement certificate or the building permit or the construction permit, by whatever name called issued by the competent authority to allow or permit the promoter to begin development works on an immovable property, as per the sanctioned plan;`
  line
  line `(n) "common areas" mean---`
  line
  line `(i) the entire land for the real estate project or where the project is developed in phases and`
  line `registration under this Act is sought for a phase, the entire land for that phase;`
  line
  line `(ii) the stair cases, lifts, staircase and lift lobbies, fire escapes, and common entrances and`
  line `exits of buildings;`
  line
  line `(iii) the common basements, terraces, parks, play areas, open parking areas and common`
  line `storage spaces;`
  line
  line `(iv) the premises for the lodging of persons employed for the management of the property`
  line `including accommodation for watch and ward staffs or for the lodging of community service`
  line personnel;
  line
  line `(v) installations of central services such as electricity, gas, water and sanitation,`
  line `air-conditioning and incinerating, system for water conservation and renewable energy;`
  line
  line `(vi) the water tanks, sumps, motors, fans, compressors, ducts and all apparatus connected`
  line `with installations for common use;`
  line
  line `(vii) all community and commercial facilities as provided in the real estate project;`
  line
  line `(viii) all other portion of the project necessary or convenient for its maintenance, safety, etc.,`
  line `and in common use;`
  line
  line `(o) "company" means a company incorporated and registered under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) and includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) a corporation established by or under any Central Act or State Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) a development authority or any public authority established by the Government in this`
  line `behalf under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(p) "competent authority" means the local authority or any authority created or established under any law for the time being in force by the appropriate Government which exercises authority over land under its jurisdiction, and has powers to give permission for development of such immovable property;`
  line
  line `(q) "completion certificate" means the completion certificate, or such other certificate, by whatever name called, issued by the competent authority certifying that the real estate project has been developed according to the sanctioned plan, layout plan and specifications, as approved by the competent authority under the local laws;`
  line
  line `(r) "day" means the working day, in the concerned State or Union territory, as the case may be, notified by the appropriate Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(s) "development" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means carrying out the development of immovable property, engineering or other operations in, on, over or under the land or the making of any material change in any immovable property or land and includes re-development;`
  line
  line `(t) "development works" means the external development works and internal development works on immovable property;`
  line
  line `(u) "engineer" means a person who possesses a bachelor's degree or equivalent from an institution recognised by the All India Council of Technical Education or any University or any institution recognised under a law or is registered as an engineer under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(v) "estimated cost of real estate project" means the total cost involved in developing the real estate project and includes the land cost, taxes, cess, development and other charges;`
  line
  line `(w) "external development works" includes roads and road systems landscaping, water supply, sewerage and drainage systems, electricity supply transformer, sub-station, solid waste management and disposal or any other work which may have to be executed in the periphery of, or outside, a project for its benefit, as may be provided under the local laws;`
  line
  line `(x) "family" includes husband, wife, minor son and unmarried daughter wholly dependent on a person;`
  line
  line `(y) "garage" means a place within a project having a roof and walls on three sides for parking any vehicle, but does not include an unenclosed or uncovered parking space such as open parking areas;`
  line
  line `(z)"immovable property" includes land, buildings, rights of ways, lights or any other benefit arising out of land and things attached to the earth or permanently fastened to anything which is attached to the earth, but not standing timber, standing crops or grass;`
  line
  line `(za) "interest" means the rates of interest payable by the promoter or the allottee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this clause---`
  line
  line `(i) the rate of interest chargeable from the allottee by the promoter, in case of default, shall be`
  line `equal to the rate of interest which the promoter shall be liable to pay the allottee, in case of`
  line default;
  line
  line `(ii) the interest payable by the promoter to the allottee shall be from the date the promoter`
  line `received the amount or any part thereof till the date the amount or part thereof and interest thereon is refunded, and the interest payable by the allottee to the promoter shall be from the date`
  line `the allottee defaults in payment to the promoter till the date it is paid;`
  line
  line `(zb) "internal development works" means roads, footpaths, water supply, sewers, drains, parks, tree planting, street lighting, provision for community buildings and for treatment and disposal of sewage and sullage water, solid waste management and disposal, water conservation, energy management, fire protection and fire safety requirements, social infrastructure such as education health and other public amenities or any other work in a project for its benefit, as per sanctioned plans;`
  line
  line `(zc) "local authority" means the Municipal Corporation or Municipality or Panchayats or any other Local Body constituted under any law for the time being in force for providing municipal services or basic services, as the case may be, in respect of areas under its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(zd) "Member" means the member of the Real Estate Regulatory Authority appointed under section 21 and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(ze) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression "notify" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(zf) "occupancy certificate" means the occupancy certificate, or such other certificate, by whatever name called, issued by the competent authority permitting occupation of any building, as provided under local laws, which has provision for civic infrastructure such as water, sanitation and electricity;`
  line
  line `(zg) "Person" includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) an individual;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Hindu undivided family;`
  line
  line `(iii) a company;`
  line
  line `(iv) a firm under the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) or the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(v) a competent authority;`
  line
  line `(vi) an association of persons or a body of individuals whether incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(vii) a co-operative society registered under any law relating to co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `(viii) any such other entity as the appropriate Government may, by notification, specify in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `(zh) "planning area" means a planning area or a development area or a local planning area or a regional development plan area, by whatever name called, or any other area specified as such by the appropriate Government or any competent authority and includes any area designated by the appropriate Government or the competent authority to be a planning area for future planned development, under the law relating to Town and Country Planning for the time being in force and as revised from time to time;`
  line
  line `(zi) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zj) "project" means the real estate project as defined in clause (zn);`
  line
  line `(zk) "promoter" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) a person who constructs or causes to be constructed an independent building or a building`
  line `consisting of apartments, or converts an existing building or a part thereof into apartments, for the`
  line `purpose of selling all or some of the apartments to other persons and includes his assignees; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a person who develops land into a project, whether or not the person also constructs`
  line `structures on any of the plots, for the purpose of selling to other persons all or some of the plots in`
  line `the said project, whether with or without structures thereon; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any development authority or any other public body in respect of allottees of---`
  line
  line `(a) buildings or apartments, as the case may be, constructed by such authority or body on`
  line `lands owned by them or placed at their disposal by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) plots owned by such authority or body or placed at their disposal by the Government,`
  line `for the purpose of selling all or some of the apartments or plots; or`
  line
  line `(iv) an apex State level co-operative housing finance society and a primary co-operative`
  line `housing society which constructs apartments or buildings for its Members or in respect of the`
  line `allottees of such apartments or buildings; or`
  line
  line `(v) any other person who acts himself as a builder, coloniser, contractor, developer, estate`
  line `developer or by any other name or claims to be acting as the holder of a power of attorney from`
  line `the owner of the land on which the building or apartment is constructed or plot is developed for`
  line `sale; or`
  line
  line `(vi) such other person who constructs any building or apartment for sale to the general public.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, where the person who constructs or converts a`
  line `building into apartments or develops a plot for sale and the person who sells apartments or plots`
  line `are different person, both of them shall be deemed to be the promoters and shall be jointly liable`
  line `as such for the functions and responsibilities specified under this Act or the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(zl) "prospectus" means any document described or issued as a prospectus or any notice, circular, or other document offering for sale of any real estate project or inviting any person to make advances or deposits for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(zm) "real estate agent" means any person, who negotiates or acts on behalf of one person in a transaction of transfer of his plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, in a real estate project, by way of sale, with another person or transfer of plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, of any other person to him and receives remuneration or fees or any other charges for his services whether as a commission or otherwise and includes a person who introduces, through any medium, prospective buyers and sellers to each other for negotiation for sale or purchase of plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, and includes property dealers, brokers, middlemen by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(zn) "real estate project" means the development of a building or a building consisting of apartments, or converting an existing building or a part thereof into apartments, or the development of land into plots or apartments, as the case may be, for the purpose of selling all or some of the said apartments or plots or building, as the case may be, and includes the common areas, the development works, all improvements and structures thereon, and all easement, rights and appurtenances belonging thereto;`
  line
  line `(zo) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zp) "rule" means the rules made under this Act by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(zq) "sanctioned plan" means the site plan, building plan, service plan, parking and circulation plan, landscape plan, layout plan, zoning plan and such other plan and includes structural designs, if applicable, permissions such as environment permission and such other permissions, which are approved by the competent authority prior to start of a real estate project;`
  line
  line `(zr) words and expressions used herein but not defined in this Act and defined in any law for the`
  line `time being in force or in the municipal laws or such other relevant laws of the appropriate`
  line `Government shall have the same meanings respectively assigned to them in those laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8627)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prior registration of real estate project with Real Estate Regulatory Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8627&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `promoter shall advertise, market, book, sell or offer for sale, or invite persons to purchase in any manner`
  line `any plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, in any real estate project or part of it, in any planning`
  line `area, without registering the real estate project with the Real Estate Regulatory Authority established`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that projects that are ongoing on the date of commencement of this Act and for which the`
  line `completion certificate has not been issued, the promoter shall make an application to the Authority for`
  line `registration of the said project within a period of three months from the date of commencement of this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Authority thinks necessary, in the interest of allottees, for projects which`
  line `are developed beyond the planning area but with the requisite permission of the local authority, it may, by`
  line `order, direct the promoter of such project to register with the Authority, and the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules and regulations made thereunder, shall apply to such projects from that stage of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no registration of the real estate project`
  line `shall be required—`
  line
  line `(a) where the area of land proposed to be developed does not exceed five hundred square meters`
  line `or the number of apartments proposed to be developed does not exceed eight inclusive of all phases:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the appropriate Government considers it necessary, it may, reduce the threshold`
  line `below five hundred square meters or eight apartments, as the case may be, inclusive of all phases, for`
  line `exemption from registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where the promoter has received completion certificate for a real estate project prior to`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of renovation or repair or re-development which does not involve marketing,`
  line `advertising selling or new allotment of any apartment, plot or building, as the case may be, under the`
  line `real estate project.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, where the real estate project is to be developed in`
  line `phases, every such phase shall be considered a stand alone real estate project, and the promoter shall`
  line `obtain registration under this Act for each phase separately.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8628)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application for registration of real estate projects.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 S.O. 3347 (E), for “specified by regulations made by the Authority” (w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8628&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every promoter shall make an`
  line `application to the Authority for registration of the real estate project in such form, manner, within such`
  line `time and accompanied by such fee as may be ^1`
  line [prescribed].
  line
  line `(2) The promoter shall enclose the following documents along with the application referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a brief details of his enterprise including its name, registered address, type of enterprise`
  line `(proprietorship, societies, partnership, companies, competent authority), and the particulars of`
  line `registration, and the names and photographs of the promoter;`
  line
  line `(b) a brief detail of the projects launched by him, in the past five years, whether already`
  line `completed or being developed, as the case may be, including the current status of the said projects,`
  line `any delay in its completion, details of cases pending, details of type of land and payments pending;`
  line
  line `(c) an authenticated copy of the approvals and commencement certificate from the competent`
  line `authority obtained in accordance with the laws as may be applicable for the real estate project`
  line `mentioned in the application, and where the project is proposed to be developed in phases, an`
  line `authenticated copy of the approvals and commencement certificate from the competent authority for`
  line `each of such phases;`
  line
  line `(d) the sanctioned plan, layout plan and specifications of the proposed project or the phase`
  line `thereof, and the whole project as sanctioned by the competent authority;`
  line
  line `(e) the plan of development works to be executed in the proposed project and the proposed`
  line `facilities to be provided thereof including fire fighting facilities, drinking water facilities, emergency`
  line `evacuation services, use of renewable energy;`
  line
  line `(f) the location details of the project, with clear demarcation of land dedicated for the project`
  line `along with its boundaries including the latitude and longitude of the end points of the project;`
  line
  line `(g) proforma of the allotment letter, agreement for sale, and the conveyance deed proposed to be`
  line `signed with the allottees;`
  line
  line `(h) the number, type and the carpet area of apartments for sale in the project along with the area`
  line `of the exclusive balcony or verandah areas and the exclusive open terrace areas appurtenant with the`
  line `apartment, if any;`
  line
  line `(i) the number and area of garage for sale in the project;`
  line
  line `(j) the names and addresses of his real estate agents, if any, for the proposed project;`
  line
  line `(k) the names and addresses of the contractors, architect, structural engineer, if any and other`
  line `persons concerned with the development of the proposed project;`
  line
  line `(l) a declaration, supported by an affidavit, which shall be signed by the promoter or any person`
  line `authorised by the promoter, stating:—`
  line
  line `(A) that he has a legal title to the land on which the development is proposed along with`
  line `legally valid documents with authentication of such title, if such land is owned by another person;`
  line
  line `(B) that the land is free from all encumbrances, or as the case may be details of the`
  line `encumbrances on such land including any rights, title, interest or name of any party in or over`
  line `such land along with details;`
  line
  line `(C) the time period within which he undertakes to complete the project or phase thereof, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(D) that seventy per cent. of the amounts realised for the real estate project from the allottees,`
  line `from time to time, shall be deposited in a separate account to be maintained in a scheduled bank`
  line `to cover the cost of construction and the land cost and shall be used only for that purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the promoter shall withdraw the amounts from the separate account, to cover`
  line `the cost of the project, in proportion to the percentage of completion of the project:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the amounts from the separate account shall be withdrawn by the`
  line `promoter after it is certified by an engineer, an architect and a chartered accountant in practice`
  line `that the withdrawal is in proportion to the percentage of completion of the project:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the promoter shall get his accounts audited within six months after the end`
  line `of every financial year by a chartered accountant in practice, and shall produce a statement of`
  line `accounts duly certified and signed by such chartered accountant and it shall be verified during the`
  line `audit that the amounts collected for a particular project have been utilised for that project and the`
  line `withdrawal has been in compliance with the proportion to the percentage of completion of the`
  line project.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this clause, the term “scheduled bank” means a bank included in the Second Scheduled to the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(E) that he shall take all the pending approvals on time, from the competent authorities;`
  line
  line `(F) that he has furnished such other documents as may be prescribed by the rules or`
  line `regulations made under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(m) such other information and documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall operationalise a web based online system for submitting applications for`
  line `registration of projects within a period of one year from the date of its establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8629)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Grant of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8629&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the application under sub-section (1) of section 4, the`
  line `Authority shall within a period of thirty days.`
  line
  line `(a) grant registration subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, and provide a registration number, including a Login Id and password to the applicant for`
  line `accessing the website of the Authority and to create his web page and to fill therein the details of the`
  line `proposed project; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application for reasons to be recorded in writing, if such application does not`
  line `conform to the provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given an opportunity`
  line `of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Authority fails to grant the registration or reject the application, as the case may be, as`
  line `provided under sub-section (1), the project shall be deemed to have been registered, and the Authority`
  line `shall within a period of seven days of the expiry of the said period of thirty days specified under`
  line `sub-section (1), provide a registration number and a Login Id and password to the promoter for accessing`
  line `the website of the Authority and to create his web page and to fill therein the details of the proposed`
  line project.
  line
  line `(3) The registration granted under this section shall be valid for a period declared by the promoter`
  line `under sub-clause (C) of clause (l) of sub-section (2) of section 4 for completion of the project or phase`
  line `thereof, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8630)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Extension of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8630&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The registration granted under section 5 may be extended by the`
  line `Authority on an application made by the promoter, due to force majeure, in such form and on payment of`
  line `such fee as may be ^1[prescribed]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority may in reasonable circumstances, without default on the part of the`
  line `promoter, based on the facts of each case, and for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the`
  line `registration granted to a project for such time as it considers necessary, which shall, in aggregate, not`
  line `exceed a period of one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application for extension of registration shall be rejected unless the applicant`
  line `has been given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this section, the expression "force majeure" shall mean a case of`
  line `war, flood, drought, fire, cyclone, earthquake or any other calamity caused by nature affecting the`
  line `regular development of the real estate project.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 S.O. 3347 (E), for "specified`
  line `by regulations made by the Authority" (w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8631)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Revocation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8631&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, on receipt of a complaint or suomotu in this`
  line `behalf or on the recommendation of the competent authority, revoke the registration granted under section`
  line `5, after being satisfied that---`
  line
  line `(a) the promoter makes default in doing anything required by or under this Act or the rules or the`
  line `regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) the promoter violates any of the terms or conditions of the approval given by the competent`
  line authority;
  line
  line `(c) the promoter is involved in any kind of unfair practice or irregularities.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --- For the purposes of this clause, the term "unfair practice means" a practice which, for the purpose of promoting the sale or development of any real estate project adopts any unfair method or unfair or deceptive practice including any of the following practices, namely:---`
  line
  line `(A) the practice of making any statement, whether in writing or by visible representation which,---`
  line
  line `(i) falsely represents that the services are of a particular standard or grade;`
  line
  line `(ii) represents that the promoter has approval or affiliation which such promoter does not`
  line have;
  line
  line `(iii) makes a false or misleading representation concerning the services;`
  line
  line `(B) the promoter permits the publication of any advertisement or prospectus whether in any`
  line `newspaper or otherwise of services that are not intended to be offered;`
  line
  line `(d) the promoter indulges in any fraudulent practices.`
  line
  line `(2) The registration granted to the promoter under section 5 shall not be revoked unless the Authority`
  line `has given to the promoter not less than thirty days notice, in writing, stating the grounds on which it is`
  line `proposed to revoke the registration, and has considered any cause shown by the promoter within the`
  line `period of that notice against the proposed revocation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority may, instead of revoking the registration under sub-section (1), permit it to remain`
  line `in force subject to such further terms and conditions as it thinks fit to impose in the interest of the`
  line `allottees, and any such terms and conditions so imposed shall be binding upon the promoter.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority, upon the revocation of the registration,---`
  line
  line `(a) shall debar the promoter from accessing its website in relation to that project and specify his`
  line `name in the list of defaulters and display his photograph on its website and also inform the other Real`
  line `Estate Regulatory Authority in other States and Union territories about such revocation or`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(b) shall facilitate the remaining development works to be carried out in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) shall direct the bank holding the project bank account, specified under sub-clause (D) of`
  line `clause (l) of sub-section (2) of section 4, to freeze the account, and thereafter take such further`
  line `necessary actions, including consequent de-freezing of the said account, towards facilitating the`
  line `remaining development works in accordance with the provisions of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) may, to protect the interest of allottees or in the public interest, issue such directions as it may`
  line `deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8632)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Obligation of Authority consequent upon lapse of or on revocation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8632&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line Upon
  line `lapse of the registration or on revocation of the registration under this Act, the Authority, may consult the`
  line `appropriate Government to take such action as it may deem fit including the carrying out of the remaining`
  line `development works by competent authority or by the association of allottees or in any other manner, as`
  line `may be determined by the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no direction, decision or order of the Authority under this section shall take effect until`
  line `the expiry of the period of appeal provided under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of revocation of registration of a project under this Act, the association`
  line `of allottees shall have the first right of refusal for carrying out of the remaining development works.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8633)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Registration of real estate agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8633&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No real estate agent shall facilitate the sale or purchase of`
  line `or act on behalf of any person to facilitate the sale or purchase of any plot, apartment or building, as the`
  line `case may be, in a real estate project or part of it, being the part of the real estate project registered under`
  line `section 3, being sold by the promoter in any planning area, without obtaining registration under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) Every real estate agent shall make an application to the Authority for registration in such form,`
  line `manner, within such time and accompanied by such fee and documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall, within such period, in such manner and upon satisfying itself of the`
  line `fulfilment of such conditions, as may be prescribed—`
  line
  line `(a) grant a single registration to the real estate agent for the entire State or Union territory, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application for reasons to be recorded in writing, if such application does not`
  line `conform to the provisions of the Act or this rules or regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) Whereon the completion of the period specified under sub-section (3), if the applicant does not`
  line `receive any communication about the deficiencies in his application or the rejection of his application, he`
  line `shall be deemed to have been registered.`
  line
  line `(5) Every real estate agent who is registered as per the provisions of this Act or the rules and`
  line `regulations made thereunder, shall be granted a registration number by the Authority, which shall be`
  line `quoted by the real estate agent in every sale facilitated by him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Every registration shall be valid for such period as may be prescribed, and shall be renewable for a`
  line `period in such manner and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any real estate agent who has been granted registration under this Act commits breach of`
  line `any of the conditions thereof or any other terms and conditions specified under this Act or any rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, or where the Authority is satisfied that such registration has been secured by`
  line `the real estate agent through misrepresentation or fraud, the Authority may, without prejudice to any other`
  line `provisions under this Act, revoke the registration or suspend the same for such period as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such revocation or suspension shall be made by the Authority unless an opportunity`
  line `of being heard has been given to the real estate agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8634)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of real estate agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8634&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every real estate agent registered under section 9 shall—`
  line
  line `(a) not facilitate the sale or purchase of any plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, in a`
  line `real estate project or part of it, being sold by the promoter in any planning area, which is not`
  line `registered with the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) maintain and preserve such books of account, records and documents as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) not involve himself in any unfair trade practices, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the practice of making any statement, whether orally or in writing or by visible`
  line `representation which—`
  line
  line `(A) falsely represents that the services are of a particular standard or grade;`
  line
  line `(B) represents that the promoter or himself has approval or affiliation which such`
  line `promoter or himself does not have;`
  line
  line `(C) makes a false or misleading representation concerning the services;`
  line
  line `(ii) permitting the publication of any advertisement whether in any newspaper or otherwise of`
  line `services that are not intended to be offered.`
  line
  line `(d) facilitate the possession of all the information and documents, as the allottee, is entitled to, at`
  line `the time of booking of any plot, apartment or building, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) discharge such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8635)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions and duties of promoter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8635&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The promoter shall, upon receiving his Login Id and`
  line `password under clause (a) of sub-section (1) or under sub-section (2) of section 5, as the case may be,`
  line `create his web page on the website of the Authority and enter all details of the proposed project as`
  line `provided under sub-section (2) of section 4, in all the fields as provided, for public viewing, including--`
  line
  line `(a) details of the registration granted by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) quarterly up-to-date the list of number and types of apartments or plots, as the case may be,`
  line booked;
  line
  line `(c) quarterly up-to-date the list of number of garages booked;`
  line
  line `(d) quarterly up-to-date the list of approvals taken and the approvals which are pending`
  line `subsequent to commencement certificate;`
  line
  line `(e) quarterly up-to-date status of the project; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other information and documents as may be specified by the regulations made by the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The advertisement or prospectus issued or published by the promoter shall mention prominently`
  line `the website address of the Authority, wherein all details of the registered project have been entered and`
  line `include the registration number obtained from the Authority and such other matters incidental thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) The promoter, at the time of the booking and issue of allotment letter shall be responsible to make`
  line `available to the allottee, the following information, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) sanctioned plans, layout plans, along with specifications, approved by the competent`
  line `authority, by display at the site or such other place as may be specified by the regulations made by the`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(b) the stage wise time schedule of completion of the project, including the provisions for civic`
  line `infrastructure like water, sanitation and electricity.`
  line
  line `(4) The promoter shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be responsible for all obligations, responsibilities and functions under the provisions of this`
  line `Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder or to the allottees as per the agreement for sale, or to`
  line `the association of allottees, as the case may be, till the conveyance of all the apartments, plots or`
  line `buildings, as the case may be, to the allottees, or the common areas to the association of allottees or`
  line `the competent authority, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the responsibility of the promoter, with respect to the structural defect or any other`
  line `defect for such period as is referred to in sub-section (3) of section 14, shall continue even after the`
  line `conveyance deed of all the apartments, plots or buildings, as the case may be, to the allottees are`
  line executed.
  line
  line `(b) be responsible to obtain the completion certificate or the occupancy certificate, or both, as`
  line `applicable, from the relevant competent authority as per local laws or other laws for the time being in`
  line `force and to make it available to the allottees individually or to the association of allottees, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(c) be responsible to obtain the lease certificate, where the real estate project is developed on a`
  line `leasehold land, specifying the period of lease, and certifying that all dues and charges in regard to the`
  line `leasehold land has been paid, and to make the lease certificate available to the association of allottees;`
  line
  line `(d) be responsible for providing and maintaining the essential services, on reasonable charges, till`
  line `the taking over of the maintenance of the project by the association of the allottees;`
  line
  line `(e) enable the formation of an association or society or co-operative society, as the case may be,`
  line `of the allottees, or a federation of the same, under the laws applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of local laws, the association of allottees, by whatever name called,`
  line `shall be formed within a period of three months of the majority of allottees having booked their plot`
  line `or apartment or building, as the case may be, in the project;`
  line
  line `(f) execute a registered conveyance deed of the apartment, plot or building, as the case may be, in`
  line `favour of the allottee along with the undivided proportionate title in the common areas to the`
  line `association of allottees or competent authority, as the case may be, as provided under section 17 of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) pay all outgoings until he transfers the physical possession of the real estate project to the`
  line `allottee or the associations of allottees, as the case may be, which he has collected from the allottees,`
  line `for the payment of outgoings (including land cost, ground rent, municipal or other local taxes, charges`
  line `for water or electricity, maintenance charges, including mortgage loan and interest on mortgages or`
  line `other encumbrances and such other liabilities payable to competent authorities, banks and financial`
  line `institutions, which are related to the project):`
  line
  line `Provided that where any promoter fails to pay all or any of the outgoings collected by him from`
  line `the allottees or any liability, mortgage loan and interest thereon before transferring the real estate`
  line `project to such allottees, or the association of the allottees, as the case may be, the promoter shall`
  line `continue to be liable, even after the transfer of the property, to pay such outgoings and penal charges,`
  line `if any, to the authority or person to whom they are payable and be liable for the cost of any legal`
  line `proceedings which may be taken therefor by such authority or person;`
  line
  line `(h) after he executes an agreement for sale for any apartment, plot or building, as the case may be,`
  line `not mortgage or create a charge on such apartment, plot or building, as the case may be, and if any`
  line `such mortgage or charge is made or created then notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, it shall not affect the right and interest of the allottee who has taken or`
  line `agreed to take such apartment, plot or building, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(5) The promoter may cancel the allotment only in terms of the agreement for sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that the allottee may approach the Authority for relief, if he is aggrieved by such`
  line `cancellation and such cancellation is not in accordance with the terms of the agreement for sale, unilateral`
  line `and without any sufficient cause.`
  line
  line `(6) The promoter shall prepare and maintain all such other details as may be specified, from time to`
  line `time, by regulations made by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8636)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Obligations of promoter regarding veracity of the advertisement or prospectus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8636&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `person makes an advance or a deposit on the basis of the information contained in the notice,`
  line `advertisement or prospectus, or on the basis of any model apartment, plot or building, as the case may be,`
  line `and sustains any loss or damage by reason of any incorrect, false statement included therein, he shall be`
  line `compensated by the promoter in the manner as provided under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person affected by such incorrect, false statement contained in the notice,`
  line `advertisement or prospectus, or the model apartment, plot or building as the case may be, intends to`
  line `withdraw from the proposed project, he shall be returned his entire investment along with interest at such`
  line `rate as may be prescribed and the compensation in the manner provided under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8637)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `No deposit or advance to be taken by promoter without first entering into agreement for sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8637&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A promoter shall not accept a sum more than ten per cent. of the cost of the apartment, plot, or`
  line `building as the case may be, as an advance payment or an application fee, from a person without first`
  line `entering into a written agreement for sale with such person and register the said agreement for sale, under`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The agreement for sale referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in such form as may be prescribed`
  line `and shall specify the particulars of development of the project including the construction of building and`
  line `apartments, along with specifications and internal development works and external development works,`
  line `the dates and the manner by which payments towards the cost of the apartment, plot, or building, as the`
  line `case may be, are to be made by the allottees and the date on which the possession of the apartment, plot or`
  line `building is to be handed over, the rates of interest payable by the promoter to the allottee and the allottee`
  line `to the promoter in case of default, and such other particulars, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8638)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Adherence to sanctioned plans and project specifications by the promoter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8638&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `proposed project shall be developed and completed by the promoter in accordance with the sanctioned`
  line `plans, layout plans and specifications as approved by the competent authorities.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law, contract or agreement, after the sanctioned plans,`
  line `layout plans and specifications and the nature of the fixtures, fittings, amenities and common areas, of the apartment, plot or building, as the case may be, as approved by the competent authority, are disclosed or`
  line `furnished to the person who agree to take one or more of the said apartment, plot or building, as the case`
  line `may be, the promoter shall not make—`
  line
  line `(i) any additions and alterations in the sanctioned plans, layout plans and specifications and the`
  line `nature of fixtures, fittings and amenities described therein in respect of the apartment, plot or`
  line `building, as the case may be, which are agreed to be taken, without the previous consent of that`
  line `person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the promoter may make such minor additions or alterations as may be required by the`
  line `allottee, or such minor changes or alterations as may be necessary due to architectural and structural`
  line `reasons duly recommended and verified by an authorised Architect or Engineer after proper declaration`
  line `and intimation to the allottee.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purpose of this clause, minor additions or alterations excludes structural`
  line `change including an addition to the area or change in height, or the removal of part of a building, or any`
  line `change to the structure, such as the construction or removal or cutting into of any wall or a part of a wall,`
  line `partition, column, beam, joist, floor including a mezzanine floor or other support, or a change to or`
  line `closing of any required means of access ingress or egress or a change to the fixtures or equipment, etc.`
  line
  line `(ii) any other alterations or additions in the sanctioned plans, layout plans and specifications of`
  line `the buildings or the common areas within the project without the previous written consent of at least`
  line `two-thirds of the allottees, other than the promoter, who have agreed to take apartments in such`
  line building.
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purpose of this clause, the allottee, irrespective of the number of apartments or`
  line `plots, as the case may be, booked by him or booked in the name of his family, or in the case of other`
  line `persons such as companies or firms or any association of individuals, etc., by whatever name called,`
  line `booked in its name or booked in the name of its associated entities or related enterprises, shall be`
  line `considered as one allottee only.`
  line
  line `(3) In case any structural defect or any other defect in workmanship, quality or provision of services`
  line `or any other obligations of the promoter as per the agreement for sale relating to such development is`
  line `brought to the notice of the promoter within a period of five years by the allottee from the date of handing`
  line `over possession, it shall be the duty of the promoter to rectify such defects without further charge, within`
  line `thirty days, and in the event of promoter's failure to rectify such defects within such time, the aggrieved`
  line `allottees shall be entitled to receive appropriate compensation in the manner as provided under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8639)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Obligations of promoter in case of transfer of a real estate project to a third party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8639&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `promoter shall not transfer or assign his majority rights and liabilities in respect of a real estate project to`
  line `a third party without obtaining prior written consent from two-third allottees, except the promoter, and`
  line `without the prior written approval of the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that such transfer or assignment shall not affect the allotment or sale of the apartments, plots`
  line `or buildings as the case may be, in the real estate project made by the erstwhile promoter.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purpose of this sub-section, the allottee, irrespective of the number of`
  line `apartments or plots, as the case may be, booked by him or booked in the name of his family, or in the case`
  line `of other persons such as companies or firms or any association of individuals, by whatever name called,`
  line `booked in its name or booked in the name of its associated entities or related enterprises, shall be`
  line `considered as one allottee only.`
  line
  line `(2) On the transfer or assignment being permitted by the allottees and the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (1), the intending promoter shall be required to independently comply with all the pending`
  line `obligations under the provisions of this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder, and the pending`
  line `obligations as per the agreement for sale entered into by the erstwhile promoter with the allottees:`
  line
  line `Provided that any transfer or assignment permitted under provisions of this section shall not result in`
  line `extension of time to the intending promoter to complete the real estate project and he shall be required to`
  line `comply with all the pending obligations of the erstwhile promoter, and in case of default, such intending promoter shall be liable to the consequences of breach or delay, as the case may be, as provided under this`
  line `Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8640)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Obligations of promoter regarding insurance of real estate project.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8640&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The promoter shall`
  line `obtain all such insurances as may be notified by the appropriate Government, including but not limited to`
  line `insurance in respect of —`
  line
  line `(i) title of the land and building as a part of the real estate project; and`
  line
  line `(ii) construction of the real estate project.`
  line
  line `(2) The promoter shall be liable to pay the premium and charges in respect of the insurance specified`
  line `in sub-section (1) and shall pay the same before transferring the insurance to the association of the`
  line allottees.
  line
  line `(3) The insurance as specified under sub-section (1) shall stand transferred to the benefit of the`
  line `allottee or the association of allottees, as the case may be, at the time of promoter entering into an`
  line `agreement for sale with the allottee.`
  line
  line `(4) On formation of the association of the allottees, all documents relating to the insurance specified`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be handed over to the association of the allottees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8641)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Transfer of title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8641&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The promoter shall execute a registered conveyance deed in favour of the`
  line `allottee along with the undivided proportionate title in the common areas to the association of the allottees`
  line `or the competent authority, as the case may be, and hand over the physical possession of the plot,`
  line `apartment of building, as the case may be, to the allottees and the common areas to the association of the`
  line `allottees or the competent authority, as the case may be, in a real estate project, and the other title`
  line `documents pertaining thereto within specified period as per sanctioned plans as provided under the local`
  line `laws:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of any local law, conveyance deed in favour of the allottee or the`
  line `association of the allottees or the competent authority, as the case may be, under this section shall be`
  line `carried out by the promoter within three months from date of issue of occupancy certificate.`
  line
  line `(2) After obtaining the occupancy certificate and handing over physical possession to the allottees in`
  line `terms of sub-section (1), it shall be the responsibility of the promoter to handover the necessary`
  line `documents and plans, including common areas, to the association of the allottees or the competent`
  line `authority, as the case may be, as per the local laws:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of any local law, the promoter shall handover the necessary documents`
  line `and plans, including common areas, to the association of the allottees or the competent authority, as the`
  line `case may be, within thirty days after obtaining the ^1`
  line `[completion] certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 S.O. 3347(E), for "occupancy"`
  line `(w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8642)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Return of amount and compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8642&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the promoter fails to complete or is unable to give`
  line `possession of an apartment, plot or building,—`
  line
  line `(a) in accordance with the terms of the agreement for sale or, as the case may be, duly completed`
  line `by the date specified therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) due to discontinuance of his business as a developer on account of suspension or revocation of`
  line `the registration under this Act or for any other reason,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable on demand to the allottees, in case the allottee wishes to withdraw from the project,`
  line `without prejudice to any other remedy available, to return the amount received by him in respect of that`
  line `apartment, plot, building, as the case may be, with interest at such rate as may be prescribed in this behalf`
  line `including compensation in the manner as provided under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an allottee does not intend to withdraw from the project, he shall be paid, by the`
  line `promoter, interest for every month of delay, till the handing over of the possession, at such rate as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The promoter shall compensate the allottees in case of any loss caused to him due to defective title`
  line `of the land, on which the project is being developed or has been developed, in the manner as provided under this Act, and the claim for compensation under this subsection shall not be barred by limitation`
  line `provided under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) If the promoter fails to discharge any other obligations imposed on him under this Act or the rules`
  line `or regulations made thereunder or in accordance with the terms and conditions of the agreement for sale,`
  line `he shall be liable to pay such compensation to the allottees, in the manner as provided under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8643)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Rights and duties of allottees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8643&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The allottee shall be entitled to obtain the information`
  line `relating to sanctioned plans, layout plans along with the specifications, approved by the competent`
  line `authority and such other information as provided in this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder`
  line `or the agreement for sale signed with the promoter.`
  line
  line `(2) The allottee shall be entitled to know stage-wise time schedule of completion of the project,`
  line `including the provisions for water, sanitation, electricity and other amenities and services as agreed to`
  line `between the promoter and the allottee in accordance with the terms and conditions of the agreement for`
  line sale.
  line
  line `(3) The allottee shall be entitled to claim the possession of apartment, plot or building, as the case`
  line `may be, and the association of allottees shall be entitled to claim the possession of the common areas, as`
  line `per the declaration given by the promoter under sub-clause (C) of clause (l) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 4.`
  line
  line `(4) The allottee shall be entitled to claim the refund of amount paid along with interest at such rate as`
  line `may be prescribed and compensation in the manner as provided under this Act, from the promoter, if the`
  line `promoter fails to comply or is unable to give possession of the apartment, plot or building, as the case`
  line `may be, in accordance with the terms of agreement for sale or due to discontinuance of his business as a`
  line `developer on account of suspension or revocation of his registration under the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) The allottee shall be entitled to have the necessary documents and plans, including that of`
  line `common areas, after handing over the physical possession of the apartment or plot or building as the case`
  line `may be, by the promoter.`
  line
  line `(6) Every allottee, who has entered into an agreement for sale to take an apartment, plot or building as`
  line `the case may be, under section 13, shall be responsible to make necessary payments in the manner and`
  line `within the time as specified in the said agreement for sale and shall pay at the proper time and place, the`
  line `share of the registration charges, municipal taxes, water and electricity charges, maintenance charges,`
  line `ground rent, and other charges, if any.`
  line
  line `(7) The allottee shall be liable to pay interest, at such rate as may be prescribed, for any delay in`
  line `payment towards any amount or charges to be paid under sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(8) The obligations of the allottee under sub-section (6) and the liability towards interest under`
  line `sub-section (7) may be reduced when mutually agreed to between the promoter and such allottee.`
  line
  line `(9) Every allottee of the apartment, plot or building as the case may be, shall participate towards the`
  line `formation of an association or society or cooperative society of the allottees, or a federation of the same.`
  line
  line `(10) Every allottee shall take physical possession of the apartment, plot or building as the case may`
  line `be, within a period of two months of the occupancy certificate issued for the said apartment, plot or`
  line `building, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(11) Every allottee shall participate towards registration of the conveyance deed of the apartment, plot`
  line `or building, as the case may be, as provided under sub-section (1) of section 17 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8644)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Real Estate Regulatory Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8644&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate`
  line `Government shall, within a period of one year from the date of coming into force of this Act, by`
  line `notification, establish an Authority to be known as the Real Estate Regulatory Authority to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred on it and to perform the functions assigned to it under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government of two or more States or Union territories may, if it deems`
  line `fit, establish one single Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the appropriate Government may, if it deems fit, establish more than one`
  line `Authority in a State or Union territory, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided also that until the establishment of a Regulatory Authority under this section, the`
  line `appropriate Government shall, by order, designate any Regulatory Authority or any officer preferably the`
  line `Secretary of the department dealing with Housing, as the Regulatory Authority for the purposes under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that after the establishment of the Regulatory Authority, all applications, complaints or`
  line `cases pending with the Regulatory Authority designated, shall stand transferred to the Regulatory`
  line `Authority so established and shall be heard from the stage such applications, complaints or cases are`
  line transferred.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with the power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8645)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Composition of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8645&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall consist of a Chairperson and not less than two`
  line `whole time Members to be appointed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8646)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Qualifications of Chairperson and Members of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8646&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson and other`
  line `Members of the Authority shall be appointed by the appropriate Government on the recommendations of`
  line `a Selection Committee consisting of the Chief Justice of the High Court or his nominee, the Secretary of`
  line `the Department dealing with Housing and the Law Secretary, in such manner as may be prescribed, from`
  line `amongst persons having adequate knowledge of and professional experience of at-least twenty years in`
  line `case of the Chairperson and fifteen years in the case of the Members in urban development, housing, real`
  line `estate development, infrastructure, economics, technical experts from relevant fields, planning, law,`
  line `commerce, accountancy, industry, management, social service, public affairs or administration:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who is, or has been, in the service of the State Government shall not be`
  line `appointed as a Chairperson unless such person has held the post of Additional Secretary to the Central`
  line `Government or any equivalent post in the Central Government or State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person who is, or has been, in the service of the State Government shall not be`
  line `appointed as a member unless such person has held the post of Secretary to the State Government or any`
  line `equivalent post in the State Government or Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8647)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8647&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and Members shall hold`
  line `office for a term not exceeding five years from the date on which they enter upon their office, or until`
  line `they attain the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier and shall not be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) Before appointing any person as a Chairperson or Member, the appropriate Government shall`
  line `satisfy itself that the person does not have any such financial or other interest as is likely to affect`
  line `prejudicially his functions as such Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8648)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Salary and allowances payable to Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8648&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The salary and allowances`
  line `payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and other Members shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed and shall not be varied to their disadvantage during their tenure.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 23, the Chairperson or a`
  line `Member, as the case may be, may,—`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing, to the appropriate Government, notice of not less`
  line `than three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 26 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any vacancy caused to the office of the Chairperson or any other Member shall be filled-up`
  line `within a period of three months from the date on which such vacancy occurs.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8649)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Administrative powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8649&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall have powers of general`
  line `superintendence and directions in the conduct of the affairs of Authority and he shall, in addition to`
  line `presiding over the meetings of the Authority, exercise and discharge such administrative powers and`
  line `functions of the Authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8650)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Members from office in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8650&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `appropriate Government may, in accordance with the procedure notified, remove from office the`
  line `Chairperson or other Members, if the Chairperson or such other Member, as the case may be,—`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence, involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or Member shall not be removed from his office on the ground specified under`
  line `clause (d) or clause (e) of sub-section (1) except by an order made by the appropriate Government after an`
  line `inquiry made by a Judge of the High Court in which such Chairperson or Member has been informed of`
  line `the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of those charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8651)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Restrictions on Chairperson or Members on employment after cessation of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8651&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson or a Member, ceasing to hold office as such, shall not—`
  line
  line `(a) accept any employment in, or connected with, the management or administration of, any`
  line `person or organisation which has been associated with any work under this Act, from the date on`
  line `which he ceases to hold office:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any employment under the`
  line `appropriate Government or a local authority or in any statutory authority or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any Central, State or provincial Act or a Government Company, as defined`
  line `under clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), which is not a promoter as`
  line `per the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) act, for or on behalf of any person or organisation in connection with any specific proceeding`
  line `or transaction or negotiation or a case to which the Authority is a party and with respect to which the`
  line `Chairperson or such Member had, before cessation of office, acted for or provided advice to the`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(c) give advice to any person using information which was obtained in his capacity as the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member and being unavailable to or not being able to be made available to the`
  line public;
  line
  line `(d) enter into a contract of service with, or accept an appointment to a board of directors of, or`
  line `accept an offer of employment with, an entity with which he had direct and significant official`
  line `dealings during his term of office as such.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and Members shall not communicate or reveal to any person any matter which`
  line `has been brought under his consideration or known to him while acting as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8652)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Officers and other employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8652&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Authority appoint such officers and employees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `efficient discharge of their functions under this Act who would discharge their functions under the general`
  line `superintendence of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and of the employees of the Authority appointed under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8653)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Meetings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8653&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall meet at such places and times, and shall follow`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, (including quorum at such`
  line `meetings), as may be specified by the regulations made by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Chairperson for any reason, is unable to attend a meeting of the Authority, any other`
  line `Member chosen by the Members present amongst themselves at the meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes by the Members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson or`
  line `in his absence, the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) The questions which come up before the Authority shall be dealt with as expeditiously as possible`
  line `and the Authority shall dispose of the same within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of the`
  line `application:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such application could not be disposed of within the said period of sixty`
  line `days, the Authority shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the application within that`
  line period.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8654)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceeding of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8654&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8655)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Filing of complaints with the Authority or the adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8655&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any aggrieved`
  line `person may file a complaint with the Authority or the adjudicating officer, as the case may be, for any`
  line `violation or contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder,`
  line `against any promoter, allottee or real estate agent, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section "person" shall include the association of allottees`
  line `or any voluntary consumer association registered under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The form, manner and fees for filing complaint under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line ^1
  line [prescribed].
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 S.O. 3347 (E), for "specified by`
  line `regulations" (w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8656)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Functions of Authority for promotion of real estate sector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8656&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall in order to`
  line `facilitate the growth and promotion of a healthy, transparent, efficient and competitive real estate sector`
  line `make recommendations to the appropriate Government or the competent authority, as the case may be,`
  line on,—
  line
  line `(a) protection of interest of the allottees, promoter and real estate agent;`
  line
  line `(b) creation of a single window system for ensuring time bound project approvals and clearances`
  line `for timely completion of the project;`
  line
  line `(c) creation of a transparent and robust grievance redressal mechanism against acts of omission`
  line `and commission of competent authorities and their officials;`
  line
  line `(d) measures to encourage investment in the real estate sector including measures to increase`
  line `financial assistance to affordable housing segment;`
  line
  line `(e) measures to encourage construction of environmentally sustainable and affordable housing,`
  line `promoting standardisation and use of appropriate construction materials, fixtures, fittings and`
  line `construction techniques;`
  line
  line `(f) measures to encourage grading of projects on various parameters of development including`
  line `grading of promoters;`
  line
  line `(g) measures to facilitate amicable conciliation of disputes between the promoters and the`
  line `allottees through dispute settlement forums set up by the consumer or promoter associations;`
  line
  line `(h) measures to facilitate digitization of land records and system towards conclusive property`
  line `titles with title guarantee;`
  line
  line `(i) to render advice to the appropriate Government in matters relating to the development of real`
  line `estate sector;`
  line
  line `(j) any other issue that the Authority may think necessary for the promotion of the real estate`
  line sector.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8657)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Advocacy and awareness measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8657&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, while formulating`
  line `a policy on real estate sector (including review of laws related to real estate sector) or any other matter,`
  line `make a reference to the Authority for its opinion on possible effect of such policy or law on real estate`
  line `sector and on the receipt of such a reference, the Authority shall within a period of sixty days of making`
  line `such reference, give its opinion to the appropriate Government, which may thereafter take further action`
  line `as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The opinion given by the Authority under sub-section (1) shall not be binding upon the`
  line `appropriate Government in formulating such policy or laws.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall take suitable measures for the promotion of advocacy, creating awareness and`
  line `imparting training about laws relating to real estate sector and policies.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8658)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8658&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Authority shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) to register and regulate real estate projects and real estate agents registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to publish and maintain a website of records, for public viewing, of all real estate projects for`
  line `which registration has been given, with such details as may be prescribed, including information`
  line `provided in the application for which registration has been granted;`
  line
  line `(c) to maintain a database, on its website, for public viewing, and enter the names and`
  line `photographs of promoters as defaulters including the project details, registration for which has been`
  line `revoked or have been penalised under this Act, with reasons therefor, for access to the general public;`
  line
  line `(d) to maintain a database, on its website, for public viewing, and enter the names and`
  line `photographs of real estate agents who have applied and registered under this Act, with such details as`
  line `may be prescribed, including those whose registration has been rejected or revoked;`
  line
  line `(e) to fix through regulations for each areas under its jurisdiction the standard fees to be levied on`
  line `the allottees or the promoter or the real estate agent, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) to ensure compliance of the obligations cast upon the promoters, the allottees and the real`
  line `estate agents under this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(g) to ensure compliance of its regulations or orders or directions made in exercise of its powers`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) to perform such other functions as may be entrusted to the Authority by the appropriate`
  line `Government as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8659)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Authority to call for information, conduct investigations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8659&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Authority`
  line `considers it expedient to do so, on a complaint or suo motu, relating to this Act or the rules or regulations`
  line `made thereunder, it may, by order in writing and recording reasons therefor call upon any promoter or`
  line `allottee or real estate agent, as the case may be, at any time to furnish in writing such information or`
  line `explanation relating to its affairs as the Authority may require and appoint one or more persons to make`
  line `an inquiry in relation to the affairs of any promoter or allottee or the real estate agent, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, while exercising`
  line `the powers under sub-section (1), the Authority shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and at`
  line `such time as may be specified by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(iii) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8660)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to issue interim orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8660&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where during an inquiry, the Authority is satisfied that an act in`
  line `contravention of this Act, or the rules and regulations made thereunder, has been committed and`
  line `continues to be committed or that such act is about to be committed, the Authority may, by order, restrain`
  line `any promoter, allottee or real estate agent from carrying on such act until the conclusion of such inquiry`
  line `or until further orders, without giving notice to such party, where the Authority deems it necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (8661)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Powers of Authority to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8661&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, for the purpose of discharging its`
  line `functions under the provisions of this Act or rules or regulations made thereunder, issue such directions`
  line `from time to time, to the promoters or allottees or real estate agents, as the case may be, as it may`
  line `consider necessary and such directions shall be binding on all concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (8662)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Powers of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8662&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall have powers to impose penalty or interest, in`
  line `regard to any contravention of obligations cast upon the promoters, the allottees and the real estate agents,`
  line `under this Act or the rules and the regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Authority shall have powers to regulate its own`
  line procedure.
  line
  line `(3) Where an issue is raised relating to agreement, action, omission, practice or procedure that`
  line
  line `(a) has an appreciable prevention, restriction or distortion of competition in connection with the`
  line `development of a real estate project; or`
  line
  line `(b) has effect of market power of monopoly situation being abused for affecting interest of`
  line `allottees adversely,`
  line
  line `then the Authority, may, suo motu, make reference in respect of such issue to the Competition`
  line `Commission of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (8663)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Rectification of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8663&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, at any time within a period of two years from the`
  line `date of the order made under this Act, with a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `amend any order passed by it, and shall make such amendment, if the mistake is brought to its notice by`
  line `the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such amendment shall be made in respect of any order against which an appeal has`
  line `been preferred under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority shall not, while rectifying any mistake apparent from record,`
  line `amend substantive part of its order passed under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (8664)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Recovery of interest or penalty or compensation and enforcement of order, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8664&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a`
  line `promoter or an allottee or a real estate agent, as the case may be, fails to pay any interest or penalty or`
  line `compensation imposed on him, by the adjudicating officer or the Regulatory Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Authority, as the case may be, under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder, it shall be`
  line `recoverable from such promoter or allottee or real estate agent, in such manner as may be prescribed as an`
  line `arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) If any adjudicating officer or the Regulatory Authority or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may`
  line `be, issues any order or directs any person to do any act, or refrain from doing any act, which it is`
  line `empowered to do under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder, then in case of failure by any`
  line `person to comply with such order or direction, the same shall be enforced, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (8665)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Establishment of Central Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8665&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, establish with effect from such date as it may specify in such notification, a Council to be`
  line `known as the Central Advisory Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Minister to the Government of India in charge of the Ministry of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with Housing shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the Central Advisory Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Advisory Council shall consist of representatives of the Ministry of Finance, Ministry`
  line `of Industry and Commerce, Ministry of Urban Development, Ministry of Consumer Affairs, Ministry of`
  line `Corporate Affairs, Ministry of Law and Justice, Niti Aayog, National Housing Bank, Housing and Urban`
  line `Development Corporation, five representatives of State Governments to be selected by rotation, five`
  line `representatives of the Real Estate Regulatory Authorities to be selected by rotation, and any other Central`
  line `Government department as notified.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Advisory Council shall also consist of not more than ten members to represent the`
  line `interests of real estate industry, consumers, real estate agents, construction labourers, non-governmental`
  line `organisations and academic and research bodies in the real estate sector.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (8666)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Functions of Central Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8666&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of the Central Advisory Council`
  line `shall be to advise and recommend the Central Government,—`
  line
  line `(a) on all matters concerning the implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) on major questions of policy;`
  line
  line `(c) towards protection of consumer interest;`
  line
  line `(d) to foster the growth and development of the real estate sector;`
  line
  line `(e) on any other matter as may be assigned to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may specify the rules to give effect to the recommendations of the`
  line `Central Advisory Council on matters as provided under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (8667)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Establishment of Real Estate Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8667&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall,`
  line `within a period of one year from the date of coming into force of this Act, by notification, establish an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal to be known as the-- (name of the State/Union territory) Real Estate Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, if it deems necessary, establish one or more benches of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, for various jurisdictions, in the State or Union territory, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Every bench of the Appellate Tribunal shall consist of at least one Judicial Member and one`
  line `Administrative or Technical Member.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government of two or more States or Union territories may, if it deems fit,`
  line `establish one single Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that, until the establishment of an Appellate Tribunal under this section, the appropriate`
  line `Government shall designate, by order, any Appellate Tribunal functioning under any law for the time`
  line `being in force, to be the Appellate Tribunal to hear appeals under the Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that after the Appellate Tribunal under this section is established, all matters pending`
  line `with the Appellate Tribunal designated to hear appeals, shall stand transferred to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `so established and shall be heard from the stage such appeal is transferred.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by any direction or decision or order made by the Authority or by an`
  line `adjudicating officer under this Act may prefer an appeal before the Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction`
  line `over the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a promoter files an appeal with the Appellate Tribunal, it shall not be entertained,`
  line `without the promoter first having deposited with the Appellate Tribunal atleast thirty per cent. of the`
  line `penalty, or such higher percentage as may be determined by the Appellate Tribunal, or the total amount to`
  line `be paid to the allottee including interest and compensation imposed on him, if any, or with both, as the`
  line `case may be, before the said appeal is heard.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section "person" shall include the association of allottees`
  line `or any voluntary consumer association registered under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (8668)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Application for settlement of disputes and appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8668&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `appropriate Government or the competent authority or any person aggrieved by any direction or order or`
  line `decision of the Authority or the adjudicating officer may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal made under sub-section (1) shall be preferred within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date on which a copy of the direction or order or decision made by the Authority or the adjudicating`
  line `officer is received by the appropriate Government or the competent authority or the aggrieved person and`
  line `it shall be in such form and accompanied by such fee, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain any appeal after the expiry of sixty days if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filling it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may after giving the parties`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders, including interim orders, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties and to the`
  line `Authority or the adjudicating officer, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal preferred under sub-section (1), shall be dealt with by it as expeditiously as possible`
  line `and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal within a period of sixty days from the date of`
  line `receipt of appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such appeal could not be disposed of within the said period of sixty days, the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(6) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of examining the legality or propriety or correctness`
  line `of any order or decision of the Authority or the adjudicating officer, on its own motion or otherwise, call`
  line `for the records relevant to deposing of such appeal and make such orders as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (8669)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Composition of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8669&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Appellate Tribunal shall consist of a Chairperson and`
  line `not less than two whole time Members of which one shall be a Judicial member and other shall be a`
  line `Technical or Administrative Member, to be appointed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this Chapter,—`
  line
  line `(i) "Judicial Member" means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal appointed as such under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(ii) "Technical or Administrative Member" means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal appointed`
  line `as such under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (8670)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8670&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be`
  line `qualified for appointment as the Chairperson or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal unless he,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of Chairperson, is or has been a Judge of a High Court; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Judicial Member he has held a judicial office in the territory of India for at`
  line `least fifteen years or has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held the post of`
  line `Additional Secretary of that service or any equivalent post, or has been an advocate for at least twenty`
  line `years with experience in dealing with real estate matters; and`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a Technical or Administrative Member, he is a person who is well-versed in the`
  line `field of urban development, housing, real estate development, infrastructure, economics, planning,`
  line `law, commerce, accountancy, industry, management, public affairs or administration and possesses`
  line `experience of at least twenty years in the field or who has held the post in the Central Government or`
  line `a State Government equivalent to the post of Additional Secretary to the Government of India or an`
  line `equivalent post in the Central Government or an equivalent post in the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal shall be appointed by the appropriate Government in`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of High Court or his nominee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Judicial Members and Technical or Administrative Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `be appointed by the appropriate Government on the recommendations of a Selection Committee`
  line `consisting of the Chief Justice of the High Court or his nominee, the Secretary of the Department`
  line `handling Housing and the Law Secretary and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (8671)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8671&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall hold office, as such for a term not exceeding five years from`
  line `the date on which he enters upon his office, but shall not be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a person, who is or has been a Judge of a High Court, has been appointed as`
  line `Chairperson of the Tribunal, he shall not hold office after he has attained the age of sixty-seven years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member shall hold office`
  line `after he has attained the age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Before appointing any person as Chairperson or Member, the appropriate Government shall`
  line `satisfy itself that the person does not have any such financial or other interest, as is likely to affect`
  line `prejudicially his functions as such member.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (8672)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Salary and allowances payable to Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8672&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The salary and allowances`
  line `payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and other Members shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed and shall not be varied to their disadvantage during their tenure.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 47, the Chairperson or a`
  line `Member, as the case may be, may:—`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the appropriate Government a notice of not less`
  line `than three months;`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 49.`
  line
  line `(3) A vacancy caused to the office of the Chairperson or any other Member, as the case may be, shall`
  line `be filled-up within a period of three months from the date on which such vacancy occurs.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (8673)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Member from office in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8673&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `appropriate Government may, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court, remove from`
  line `office of the Chairperson or any Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, who—`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the appropriate Government`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member shall not be`
  line `removed from his office except by an order made by the appropriate Government after an inquiry made`
  line `by the Judge of the High Court in which such Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or`
  line `Administrative Member has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may suspend from the office of the Chairperson or Judicial Member`
  line `or Technical or Administrative Member in respect of whom a reference of conducting an inquiry has been`
  line `made to the Judge of the High Court under sub-section (2), until the appropriate Government passes an`
  line `order on receipt of the report of inquiry made by the Judge of the High Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for inquiry referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (8674)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Restrictions on Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member on employment after cessation of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8674&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or`
  line `Administrative Member, ceasing to hold office as such shall not:—`
  line
  line `(a) accept any employment in, or connected with, the management or administration of, any`
  line `person or organisation which has been associated with any work under this Act, from the date on`
  line `which he ceases to hold office:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any employment under the`
  line `appropriate Government or a local authority or in any statutory authority or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government Company as defined`
  line `under clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), which is not a promoter as`
  line `per the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) act, for or on behalf of any person or organisation in connection with any specific proceeding`
  line `or transaction or negotiation or a case to which the Authority is a party and with respect to which the`
  line `Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member had, before cessation of`
  line `office, acted for or provided advice to, the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) give advice to any person using information which was obtained in his capacity as the`
  line `Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member and being unavailable to or`
  line `not being able to be made available to the public;`
  line
  line `(d) enter into a contract of service with, or accept an appointment to a board of directors of, or`
  line `accept an offer of employment with, an entity with which he had direct and significant official`
  line `dealings during his term of office as such.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or Judicial Member or Technical or Administrative Member shall not`
  line `communicate or reveal to any person any matter which has been brought under his consideration or`
  line `known to him while acting as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (8675)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Officers and other employees of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8675&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall`
  line `provide the Appellate Tribunal with such officers and employees as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of its Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (8676)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title Vacancies.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8676&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If, for reason other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in the office of the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal, the appropriate Government shall appoint another`
  line `person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the vacancy and the proceedings may be`
  line `continued before the Appellate Tribunal from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (8677)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8677&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid down`
  line `by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own`
  line procedure.
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Tribunal shall also not be bound by the rules of evidence contained in the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purpose of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examinations of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or directing it ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) All proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193, 219 and 228 for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860), and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be civil court for the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (8678)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Administrative powers of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8678&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall have`
  line `powers of general superintendence and direction in the conduct of the affairs of Appellate Tribunal and he`
  line `shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of the Appellate Tribunal, exercise and discharge such`
  line `administrative powers and functions of the Appellate Tribunal as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (8679)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceeding of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8679&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Appellate Tribunal not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (8680)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8680&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The applicant or appellant may either appear in person or`
  line `authorise one or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal`
  line `practitioners or any of its officers to present his or its case before the Appellate Tribunal or the Regulatory`
  line `Authority or the adjudicating officer, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force and who has obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force and who has obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) or any other law for the time being in force and who has obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(d) "legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or an attorney of any High Court, and includes a`
  line `pleader in practice.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (8681)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Orders passed by Appellate Tribunal to be executable as a decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8681&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every order made by`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Appellate Tribunal as a decree of civil`
  line `court, and for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if`
  line `it were a decree made by the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (8682)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8682&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, may, file an appeal to the High Court, within a period of sixty days from the date of`
  line `communication of the decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal, to him, on any one or more of the`
  line `grounds specified in section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of sixty days,`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The expression "High Court" means the High Court of a State or Union territory`
  line `where the real estate project is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie against any decision or order made by the Appellate Tribunal with the consent`
  line `of the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (8683)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Punishment for nonregistration under section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8683&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any promoter contravenes the`
  line `provisions of section 3, he shall be liable to a penalty which may extend up to ten per cent. of the`
  line `estimated cost of the real estate project as determined by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If any promoter does not comply with the orders, decisions or directions issued under sub-section`
  line `(1) or continues to violate the provisions of section 3, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend up to three years or with fine which may extend up to a further ten per cent. of the`
  line `estimated cost of the real estate project, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (8684)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8684&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `If any promoter provides false information or`
  line `contravenes the provisions of section 4, he shall be liable to a penalty which may extend up to five per`
  line `cent. of the estimated cost of the real estate project, as determined by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (8685)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Penalty for contravention of other provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8685&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `If any promoter contravenes any`
  line `other provisions of this Act, other than that provided under section 3 or section 4, or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, he shall be liable to a penalty which may extend up to five per cent. of the`
  line `estimated cost of the real estate project as determined by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (8686)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Penalty for nonregistration and contravention under sections 9 and 10.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8686&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `If any real estate`
  line `agent fails to comply with or contravenes the provisions of section 9 or section 10, he shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty of ten thousand rupees for every day during which such default continues, which may`
  line `cumulatively extend up to five per cent. of the cost of plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, of`
  line `the real estate project, for which the sale or purchase has been facilitated as determined by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (8687)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Authority by promoter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8687&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If any promoter, who`
  line `fails to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders or directions of the Authority, he shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty for every day during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend up to five per`
  line `cent., of the estimated cost of the real estate project as determined by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (8688)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Appellate Tribunal by promoter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8688&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `promoter, who fails to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders, decisions or directions of the Appellate Tribunal, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend up to three`
  line `years or with fine for every day during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend up`
  line `to ten per cent. of the estimated cost of the real estate project, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (8689)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Authority by real estate agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8689&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `If any real estate`
  line `agent, who fails to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders or directions of the Authority, he shall`
  line `be liable to a penalty for every day during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend`
  line `up to five per cent., of the estimated cost of plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, of the real`
  line `estate project, for which the sale or purchase has been facilitated and as determined by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (8690)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Appellate Tribunal by real estate agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8690&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `real estate agent, who fails to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders, decisions or directions of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend up to one year`
  line `or with fine for every day during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend up to ten`
  line `per cent. of the estimated cost of plot, apartment or building, as the case may be, of the real estate project,`
  line `for which the sale or purchase has been facilitated, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (8691)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Authority by allottee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8691&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `If any allottee, who fails`
  line `to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders, decisions or directions of the Authority he shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty for the period during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend up`
  line `to five per cent. of the plot, apartment or building cost, as the case may be, as determined by the`
  line Authority.
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (8692)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Appellate Tribunal by allottee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8692&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `If any allottee,`
  line `who fails to comply with, or contravenes any of the orders or directions of the Appellate Tribunal, as the`
  line `case may be, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend up to one year or`
  line `with fine for every day during which such default continues, which may cumulatively extend up to ten per`
  line `cent. of the plot, apartment or building cost, as the case may be, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (8693)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8693&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an Offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time, the offence was committed was in charge of, or was responsible`
  line `to the company for the conduct of, the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section, shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm, or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (8694)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8694&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), if any person is punished with imprisonment under this Act, the punishment`
  line `may, either before or after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded by the court on such terms`
  line `and conditions and on payment of such sums as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sum prescribed shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine`
  line `which may be imposed for the offence so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (8695)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8695&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging compensation under sections 12, 14, 18`
  line `and section 19, the Authority shall appoint, in consultation with the appropriate Government, one or more`
  line `judicial officer as deemed necessary, who is or has been a District Judge to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, after giving any person concerned a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person whose complaint in respect of matters covered under sections 12, 14, 18 and`
  line `section 19 is pending before the Consumer Disputes Redressal Forum or the Consumer Disputes`
  line `Redressal Commission or the National Consumer Redressal Commission, established under section 9 of`
  line `the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986), on or before the commencement of this Act, he may,`
  line `with the permission of such Forum or Commission, as the case may be, withdraw the complaint pending`
  line `before it and file an application before the adjudicating officer under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The application for adjudging compensation under sub-section (1), shall be dealt with by the`
  line `adjudicating officer as expeditiously as possible and dispose of the same within a period of sixty days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such application could not be disposed of within the said period of sixty`
  line `days, the adjudicating officer shall record his reasons in writing for not disposing of the application within`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(3) While holding an inquiry the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to`
  line `the subject matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to comply`
  line `with the provisions of any of the sections specified in sub-section (1), he may direct to pay such`
  line `compensation or interest, as the case any be, as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of any of`
  line `those sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (8696)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Factors to be taken into account by the adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8696&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `While adjudging the quantum`
  line `of compensation or interest, as the case may be, under section 71, the adjudicating officer shall have due`
  line `regard to the following factors, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a`
  line `result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of loss caused as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the default;`
  line
  line `(d) such other factors which the adjudicating officer considers necessary to the case in furtherance`
  line `of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (8697)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8697&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament in this behalf, make to the Authority grants and loans of such sums of`
  line `money as that Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (8698)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Grants and loans by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8698&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by State Legislature by law in this behalf, make to the Authority, grants and loans of such sums of`
  line `money as the State Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (8699)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Constitution of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8699&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall constitute a fund to be called the`
  line `'Real Estate Regulatory Fund' and there shall be credited thereto,—`
  line
  line `(a) all Government grants received by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) the fees received under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the interest accrued on the amounts referred to in clauses (a) to (b).`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and other Members, the adjudicating`
  line `officer and the administrative expenses including the salaries and allowances payable to the officers`
  line `and other employees of the Authority and the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the other expenses of the Authority in connection with the discharge of its functions and for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be administered by a committee of such Members of the Authority as may be`
  line `determined by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee appointed under sub-section (3) shall spend monies out of the Fund for carrying`
  line `out the objects for which the Fund has been constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (8700)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Crediting sums realised by way of penalties to Consolidated Fund of India or State account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8700&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) All sums realised, by way of penalties, imposed by the Appellate Tribunal or the`
  line `Authority, in the Union territories, shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line
  line `(2) All sums realised, by way of penalties, imposed by the Appellate Tribunal or the Authority, in a`
  line `State, shall be credited to such account as the State Government may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (8701)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Budget, accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8701&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall prepare a budget, maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Authority under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular shall have the right to demand and`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers, and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the appropriate Government by the Authority and the appropriate Government shall cause the`
  line `audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament or, as the`
  line `case may be, before the State Legislature or the Union territory Legislature, where it consists of two`
  line `Houses, or where such legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (8702)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8702&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall prepare once in every year, in such form and at such`
  line `time as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government,—`
  line
  line `(a) a description of all the activities of the Authority for the previous year;`
  line
  line `(b) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line
  line `(c) the programmes of work for the coming year.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament or, as the case may be, before the State Legislature or the`
  line `Union Territory Legislature, where it consists of two Houses, or where such legislature consists of one`
  line `House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (8703)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8703&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding in`
  line `respect of any matter which the Authority or the adjudicating officer or the Appellate Tribunal is`
  line `empowered by or under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other`
  line `authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (8704)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8704&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder save on a complaint in writing made by the Authority`
  line `or by any officer of the Authority duly authorised by it for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (8705)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8705&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any member,`
  line `officer of the Authority or any other person subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the`
  line `order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the power to make regulations under`
  line `section 85), as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (8706)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Power of appropriate Government to supersede Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8706&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the`
  line `appropriate Government is of the opinion,---`
  line
  line `(a) that, on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Authority, it is unable to discharge`
  line `the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by the`
  line `appropriate Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial`
  line `position of the Authority or the administration of the Authority has suffered; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the appropriate Government may, by notification, supersede the Authority for such period, not exceeding`
  line `six months, as may be specified in the notification and appoint a person or persons as the President or the`
  line `Governor, as the case may be, may direct to exercise powers and discharge functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the appropriate Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Authority to make representations against the proposed supersession and`
  line `shall consider the representations, if any, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Authority,---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson and other Members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their`
  line `offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the person or persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), vest in the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the appropriate Government shall reconstitute the Authority by a fresh appointment of its`
  line `Chairperson and other members and in such case any person who had vacated his office under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government shall cause a copy of the notification issued under sub-section (1)`
  line `and a full report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament or, as the case may be, before the State Legislature, or the Union Territory Legislature, as the case may be, where it consists of two Houses, or where such legislature`
  line `consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (8707)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Powers of appropriate Government to issue directions to Authority and obtain reports and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8707&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in exercise of`
  line `its powers and in performance of its functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of`
  line `policy, as the appropriate Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the appropriate Government and the Authority as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy, the decision of the appropriate Government thereon shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall furnish to the appropriate Government such returns or other information with`
  line `respect to its activities as the appropriate Government may, from time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (8708)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8708&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall,`
  line `within a period of six months of the commencement of this Act, by notification, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the form, time and manner of making application and fees payable therewith under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ab) information and documents for application to the Authority for registration under clause (m)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ac) the form of application and the fees for extension of registration under section 6;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner of making application and fee and documents to be accompanied with`
  line `such application as under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the period, manner and conditions under which the registration is to be granted under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the validity of the period of registration and the manner and fee for renewal under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance and preservation of books of account, records and documents under`
  line `clause (b) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) the discharge of other functions by the real estate agent under clause (e) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the rate of interest payable under section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and particulars of agreement for sale under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the rate of interest payable under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(j) the rate of interest payable under sub-section (4) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(k) the rate of interest payable under sub-section (7) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of selection of Chairperson and Members of Authority under section 22;`
  line
  line `(m) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and other Members of the Authority under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(n) the administrative powers of the Chairpersons under section 25;`
  line
  line `(o) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Authority under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `^2[(oa) the form, manner and fees for filing of a complaint under sub-section (2) of section 31];`
  line
  line `(p) the details to be published on the website as under clause (b) and under clause (d) of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(q) the additional functions which may be performed by the Authority under clause (iv) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner of recovery of interest, penalty and compensation under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 40;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of implementation of the order, direction or decisions of the adjudicating officer,`
  line `the Authority or the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (2) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(t) recommendations received from the Central Advisory Council under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 42;`
  line
  line `(u) the form and manner and fee for filing of appeal under sub-section (2) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of selection of Members of the Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(w) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and other Members of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(x) the procedure for inquiry of the charges against the Chairperson or Judicial Member of the`
  line `Tribunal under sub-section (4) of section 49;`
  line
  line `(y) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(z) any other powers of the Tribunal under clause (g) of sub-section (4) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(za) the powers of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal under section 54;`
  line
  line `(zb) the terms and conditions and the payment of such sum for compounding of the offences`
  line `under section 70;`
  line
  line `(zc) the manner of inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 71;`
  line
  line `(zd) the form to be specified in which the Authority shall prepare a budget, maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 77;`
  line
  line `(ze) the form in which and time at which the Authority shall prepare an annual report under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(zf) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . Subs. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 [S.O. 3347(E)], for clause (a)`
  line `(w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
  line
  line `2 . Ins. by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 [S.O. 3347(E)],`
  line `(w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (8709)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Removal of Difficulties Order, 2016 [S.O. 3347(E)] (w.e.f. 28-10-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8709&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, within a period of three months of its`
  line `establishment, by notification, make regulations, consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line ^1******
  line
  line `(c) such other information and documents required under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) display of sanctioned plans, layout plans along with specifications, approved by the competent`
  line `authority, for display under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) preparation and maintenance of other details under sub-section (6) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) time, places and the procedure in regard to transaction of business at the meetings of the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (1) of section 29;`
  line
  line ^1******
  line
  line `(h) standard fees to be levied on the promoter, the allottees or the real estate agent under`
  line `clause (e) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulation or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (8710)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Third Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 3807(E) dated (26-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8710&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made by the Central Government, every regulation made by the`
  line `Authority under the Union territory of Delhi and the Union territories without Legislature and every`
  line `notification issued by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or regulation or in the notification, as the case may be, or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule or regulation or the notification should not be made, the rule or regulation or notification, as the`
  line `case may be, shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation or notification, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by a State Government or the Union territory Government, as the case may be,`
  line `every regulation made by the Authority under the State Government or ^1[ the Union territory Government of`
  line `Puducherry or the Union territory Government of Jammu and Kashmir], as the case may be, and every notification issued by the State Government or ^1[the Union`
  line `territory Government of Puducherry or the Union territory Government of Jammu and Kashmir], as the case may be, under this Act, shall be laid as soon as may be,`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature, or the Union territory Legislature, as the case may be, where`
  line `it consists of two Houses, or where such legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (8711)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8711&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Authority, and the Appellate Tribunal and the adjudicating officer shall be deemed to be`
  line `public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (8712)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8712&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (8713)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8713&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect, notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (8714)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8714&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the appropriate Government or the Authority or any officer of the appropriate Government or`
  line `any member, officer or other employees of the Authority for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (8715)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8715&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (8716)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405&sectionId=8716&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00033_201616_1517807328405
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `The Maharashtra Housing (Regulation and Development) Act, 2012 (Maharashtra Act`
  line `No. II of 2014) is hereby repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
